api_list.name: get_payable_by_id_payables__payable_id__get
api_list.description: Retrieves information about a specific payable with the given ID.

schema.title: PayableResponseSchema

id.title: Id
id.description: A unique ID assigned to this payable.

entity_id.title: Entity Id
entity_id.description: The ID of the entity to which the payable was issued.

source_of_payable_data.description: Specifies how the property values of this payable were provided: `ocr` - Monite OCR service extracted the values from the provided PDF or image file, `user_specified` - values were added or updated via an API call.

currency.description: The [currency code](https://docs.monite.com/docs/currencies) of the currency used in the payable.

amount.title: Amount
amount.description: The total amount to be paid, in [minor units](https://docs.monite.com/docs/currencies#minor-units). For example, $12.50 is represented as 1250.

description.title: Description
description.description: An arbitrary description of this payable.

due_date.title: Due Date
due_date.description: The date by which the payable must be paid, in the YYYY-MM-DD format. If the payable specifies payment terms with early payment discounts, this is the final payment date.

issued_at.title: Issued At
issued_at.description: The date when the payable was issued, in the YYYY-MM-DD format.

counterpart_bank_id.title: Counterpart Bank Id
counterpart_bank_id.description: SWIFT code (BIC) of the vendor's bank (if specified in the payable document).

counterpart_id.title: Counterpart Id
counterpart_id.description: The ID of the counterpart object that represents the vendor or supplier.

counterpart_account_id.title: Counterpart Account Id
counterpart_account_id.description: Vendor's bank account number, IBAN, or similar (if specified in the payable document).

payable_origin.description: Specifies how this payable was created in Monite: `upload` - created via an API call, `email` - sent via email to the entity's mailbox.

was_created_by_external_user_name.title: Was Created By External User Name

was_created_by_external_user_id.title: Was Created By External User Id

file.title: File

allOf.title: FileSchema

id.title: Id
id.description: A unique ID of this file.

created_at.title: Created At
created_at.description: UTC date and time when this workflow was uploaded to Monite. Timestamps follow the [ISO 8601](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601) format.

file_type.title: File Type
file_type.description: The type of the business object associated with this file.

region.title: Region
region.description: Geographical region of the data center where the file is stored.

md5.title: Md5
md5.description: The MD5 hash of the file.

url.title: Url
url.description: The URL to download the file.

previews.title: Previews

items.title: PreviewSchema
items.description: A preview image generated for a file.

previews.description: Preview images generated for this file. There can be multiple images with different sizes.

allOf.description: Represents a file (such as a PDF invoice) that was uploaded to Monite.

file.description: The original file from which this payable was created.

tags.title: Tags

items.title: TagReadSchema

id.title: Id
id.description: A unique ID of this tag.

items.description: Represents a user-defined tag that can be assigned to payables to filter them.

tags.description: A list of user-defined tags (labels) assigned to this payable. Tags can be used to trigger a specific approval policy for this payable.

created_at.title: Created At
created_at.description: UTC date and time when this payable was created. Timestamps follow the [ISO 8601](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601) format.

updated_at.title: Updated At
updated_at.description: UTC date and time when this payable was last updated. Timestamps follow the [ISO 8601](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601) format.

other_extracted_data.title: Other Extracted Data
other_extracted_data.description: Data extracted from the uploaded payable by OCR.

applied_policy.title: Applied Policy
applied_policy.description: The name of an existing workflow (approval policy) that applies to this payable, if any. A workflow is applied if the payable matches the workflow trigger conditions.

schema.description: Represents an Accounts Payable document received from a vendor or supplier.
